## Errors & Mistakes (the valuable part)
1. pydantic CANNOT validate a foreign BaseModel instance (no from_attributes):
   tsi.X into sdk.X raises. This killed the lenient-coercion idea and forced
   the explicit tests bridge. Verified empirically before building.
2. Subclassing an SDK model to add started_at LOSES the field in NESTED
   serialization (parent-typed field serializes by parent schema). extra=allow
   extras DO survive nested dumps — that's why started_at rides as an extra
   field, not a subclass.
3. tsi SummaryInsertMap is a TypedDict(total=False): usage key present-but-None
   is INVALID. SDK dumps include None fields by default -> bridge must dump
   with exclude_none=True (matches the SDK's own wire encoding).
4. SDK models declare fields in sorted order; the caching middleware's
   prefix-invalidation matched the serialized request's LEADING fields ->
   silently stale obj_read cache after alias reassignment. Fixed with explicit
   ordered cache keys (_obj_read_cache_key/_obj_create_cache_key). This bug
   produced NO error — only wrong data. Beware serialization-order coupling.
5. SDK Query field is `expr` (tsi: `expr_`); operand lists are list[Any] so
   leaf operands stay raw dicts after validation. saved_view needed _parse_operand
   on access. ALSO means serialized Monitor queries lose _type metadata —
   golden updated; old stored objects still deserialize fine.
6. get_feedback's isinstance(query, Query) silently no-op'd the filter when
   tests passed tsi.Query (returned ALL feedback — silent wrong-data again).
   Public boundaries now coerce any BaseModel via dump/validate.
7. Strictness regression: SDK models allow extras, so bad filter keys stopped
   raising. casting.py rejects unknown dict keys explicitly (test intent
   preserved per tests-only-tighten).
8. Test chain walker: THREE wrappers forward attributes (ServerRecorder
   __getattribute__, DelegatingTraceServerMixin, TestOnlyFlushingTraceServer
   __getattr__) — getattr probing tunnels through layers and SKIPS them. Probe
   vars(current) instead, and know the attr per wrapper (_server, _tsi_server,
   server, _next_trace_server, _internal_trace_server).

